## Security Boundaries

### Never Do

- Write API keys, tokens, or passwords to any file
- Stage .env, credentials, certificates, or key files for commit
- Bypass git hook verification on any git command
- Force push to main/master
- Run recursive forced deletion without explicit user confirmation
- Skip pre-commit hooks or linter checks

### Always Do

- Use parameterized queries for all database operations
- Validate and sanitize user input at system boundaries
- Use environment variables for secrets, never hardcoded values
- Prefer `git revert` over `git reset --hard` (preserves history)

